AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 68,
relative to designation as a critical access hospital.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Short title.
This act is known and may be cited as the "Restoring Rural Hospital Access for
Perry and Decatur Counties Act."
SECTION 2. Findings.
The general assembly finds that:
(1) Rural hospitals provide essential healthcare services to this state's
most vulnerable populations and are often the only point of access to medical
care in their respective regions;
(2) Perry County Community Hospital and Decatur County General
Hospital have been fundamental in delivering healthcare services in Linden and
Parsons, respectively;
(3) Both Perry County Community Hospital and Decatur County General
Hospital previously served their respective communities as necessary providers
of healthcare services to area residents for many years, including years that
precede January 1, 2006; and
(4) The designation of these hospitals as critical access hospitals is vital
for their operational stability and for the enhancement of healthcare services in
rural Tennessee.
SECTION 3. Declaration as necessary providers.
