(a) The general assembly declares that the following are necessary providers of
healthcare services to area residents:
(1) Perry County Community Hospital, located in Linden, Tennessee; and
(2) Decatur County General Hospital, located in Parsons, Tennessee.
(b) Through its declaration in subsection (a), the general assembly recognizes
the indispensable role these hospitals play in their respective communities, and
acknowledges that prior to their closures both hospitals acted as necessary providers of
healthcare services, including during a number of years prior to 2006.
SECTION 4. Purpose.
The purpose and intent of this act is to enable Perry County Community Hospital
and Decatur County General Hospital to qualify for federal designation as critical access
hospitals pursuant to criteria established in Section 1820 of the Social Security Act (42
U.S.C. ยง 1395i-4), ensuring that those hospitals may receive the support and resources
needed to continue providing critical healthcare services.
SECTION 5. Implementation.
(a) The department of health and the health facilities commission shall take all
necessary steps to facilitate the designation of Perry County Community Hospital and
Decatur County General Hospital as critical access hospitals.
(b) The department of health and health facilities commission shall coordinate
with relevant federal agencies to ensure compliance with federal requirements and to
expedite the process of designation of Perry County Community Hospital and Decatur
County General Hospital as critical access hospitals and the delivery of the consequent
benefits of such designation.
SECTION 6. If any provision of this act or its application to any person or circumstance
is held invalid, then the invalidity does not affect other provisions or applications of the act that
